The President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), is currently playing host to the Libyan Prime Minister,  Abdul Hamid Dbeibeh, at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. Dbeibeh who arrived at the forecourt of the Presidential Villa at 10am was received by the President alongside members of his cabinet, including the Minister of Foreign Affairs, Geoffery Onyeama. Both leaders are having bilateral talks that portend favourable outcomes for both countries. More details soon…